    • addMul

      Vector3dInterface addMul​(double scalar, Vector3dInterface other)
      Scalar x vector multiplication, followed by an addition
      Parameters:
      scalar - the double used in the multiplication step
      other - the vector used in the multiplication step
      Returns:
      the result of the multiplication step added to this vector, for example: Vector3d a = Vector(); double h = 2; Vector3d b = Vector(); ahb = a.addMul(h, b); ahb should now contain the result of this mathematical operation: a+h*b
